description: Once the tariffs come into effect, they will be definitive and last for five years. The extra duties also apply, at various rates, to vehicles made in China by foreign groups such as Tesla, which faces a tariff of 7.8%. One of China's largest sellers of EVs, Geely, faces an extra duty of 18.8 %, while SAIC will be hit with the highest at 35.3%.
title: EU slaps extra tariffs of up to 35.3% on Chinese EVs

description: Every day, between 32 and 40 planes – only slightly fewer than usual for this time of year – are taking off and landing at the Lebanese capital's airport despite nearby Israeli army strikes, which have so far spared the airport.
title: Middle East Airlines, the only airline providing an air bridge between Beirut and the rest of the world

description: In front of the kingdom's parliament, the French president received a standing ovation after reiterating his recognition of 'Moroccan sovereignty' over Western Sahara.
title: In Rabat, Emmanuel Macron proposes a 'new strategic framework' with Morocco

description: Canadian David DePape, a former nudist activist and part-time carpenter, had initially planned to target Nancy, but instead encountered her husband Paul Pelosi, who was 82 at the time of the 2022 assault. The 44-year-old was already serving a 30-year federal sentence when he received life in prison without parole on Tuesday.
title: Nancy Pelosi's husband's attacker jailed for life

description: The case concerns a March 2016 incident, in which businessman Alain Dumenil accused French foreign intelligence service agents, at the time operating under Bernard Bajolet, of trying to extort €15 million from him.
title: Former French intelligence chief to face extortion trial

description: The Sunday rally featured racist and sexist remarks, including comedian Tony Hinchcliffe calling Puerto Rico a 'floating island of garbage.' Despite being urged to apologize, Trump called the event 'an absolute lovefest.'
title: US election: Trump forgoes apology for racist remarks at NYC rally

description: Taha O., a 22-year-old Moroccan national who has been suspected of killing a student outside Paris, in September, 'decided to accept extradition' from Switzerland to France, according to his lawyer.
title: Paris student murder: Suspect agrees to extradition to France

description: In the United States, an electoral college of 538 members is designated by the states, based on their population. These electors vote for the president in the months following election day.
title: US presidential election 2024: How the Electoral College works

description: 'Strava Leaks' (3/3). Three of the world's most important leaders have been put in danger due to their security guards' use of a sports social media, Strava. In this third installment of our investigation, we look into Vladimir Putin's bodyguards and their strolls around the luxurious properties that the Kremlin denies owning.
title: Stravaleaks or the security of heads of state betrayed by their bodyguards. Episode 3: The Kremlin

description: French President Emmanuel Macron said French companies 'will support the development' of the disputed territory during a visit to Morocco.
title: Macron pledges French investment in Western Sahara under 'Moroccan sovereignty'

description: With the pro-European coalition calling for a new election and refusing to take its seat in Parliament, Hungarian Prime Minister Viktor Orban, president of the Council of the EU, arrived in Tbilisi on Monday to support the ruling party.
title: Georgian opposition seeks a strategy after disputed election results

description: This will be the first edition of the men's race since 2020 to take place exclusively in France, as the routes for both the men's and women's races were revealed in Paris on Tuesday.
title: Men's Tour de France 'comes home' in 2025, as women's Tour gets tougher

description: Since October 6, the Israeli military has conducted a sweeping air and ground assault in northern Gaza, particularly in the areas of Jabalia, Beit Lahia and Beit Hanoun, in what it describes as an operation to prevent Hamas militants from regrouping.
title: Israeli airstrike in northern Gaza kills at least 93, reports civil defense agency

description: In Basel on Sunday, the 21-year-old French player won the biggest title of his young career. On Tuesday, the new world No. 31 will take on the American Frances Tiafoe at the Paris Masters.
title: 'When I have the ball, I want to inflict pain': Giovanni Mpetshi Perricard, more than just a supersonic serve

description: Bannon, 70, reported to the prison on July 1 after the Supreme Court rejected his bid to delay the prison sentence while he appeals his conviction.
title: Trump ally Steve Bannon released after four months in prison for contempt of Congress

description: The NGO analyzed a sample of almost 150 cans from 15 European supermarkets. One in 10 cans tested showed mercury levels above the authorized limits for fresh tuna.
title: French NGO warns of canned tuna 'health scandal' over mercury levels

description: At a time when the Gaza Strip is undergoing the worst humanitarian crisis in its history, Israel's parliament adopted legislation designed to compromise the activities of the UN agency for Palestinian refugees in the enclave and also in the occupied West Bank and East Jerusalem.
title: Israel's UNRWA ban: Unprecedented decision jeopardizes aid to Palestinians as war rages

description: While a number of legal experts are now claiming that Israel committed war crimes and crimes against humanity, given the scale of the destruction in Gaza, the question of systematic genocidal actions is more controversial.
title: Gaza genocide accusation constitutes unprecedented test for international justice

description: A United Nations report published during COP16, which is being held in Colombia, asserts that the surface area of protected zones must double on land and triple at sea over the next six years.
title: Biodiversity: The world is not on track to protect 30% of land and sea by 2030

description: Kassem was one of Hezbollah's founders in 1982 and has been the party's deputy secretary general since 1991. He succeeds Hassan Nasrallah after he was assassinated in an Israeli strike on Beirut last month.
title: Hezbollah names Naim Kassem as new leader

description: The US is holding its breath, as the Republican candidate's methods have been known since 2020: unfounded proclamation of victory, possible local blockades by his supporters of the certification of results, judicial warfare and even violence.
title: Donald Trump is once again ready to do anything to challenge the outcome if defeated

description: Reince Priebus, Scott Walker and Paul Ryan, three promising elected officials from the Midwest, did not politically survive Donald Trump's tumultuous exercise of power.
title: The disillusionment of the Wisconsin Three after Trump's 2016 takeover of the GOP

description: The 75-year-old actor, who was due to stand trial on Monday, was absent for health reasons. The trial has been postponed until March 2025. However, his lawyer took advantage of the hearing to begin arguing the merits of the case.
title: Gérard Depardieu's trial: His lawyer's closing arguments before the closing arguments

description: With the recession in Germany spreading to the automotive supply chain, and the difficulty of making the transition to a service economy, the small Balkan state illustrates the slowdown in growth in countries that joined the European Union in 2004.
title: Slovenia caught in the German slowdown trap

description: The Red List drawn up by the International Union for Conservation of Nature and updated on the occasion of the COP16 biodiversity held in Cali, Colombia, has warned of the pressures on trees.
title: Over one in three tree species is at risk of extinction worldwide
